The paper discusses reinforcement learning (RL) with human feedback, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with RL algorithms and their application to robotics. The second likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper discusses the challenges of applying RL to robotics and proposes a method to overcome them. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new RL method and compares it to existing ones. The fourth likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), as the paper discusses the use of human feedback in RL and proposes a method to model it. The fifth likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper demonstrates a real-world application of human-in-the-loop RL that uses facial expression recognition.
